3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit calculates SUI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The funding fee is exchanged directly between long and short position holders, with no exchange commission. Bybit caps funding rates at ±0.75% per interval to prevent extreme scenarios, though SUI rarely approaches these limits."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SUI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT offers compelling funding arbitrage due to the token's volatility and growing ecosystem adoption. Layer 1 tokens like SUI often experience sustained directional bias during network upgrades or partnership announcements, creating persistent funding rate imbalances. The mid-tier trading volume provides sufficient liquidity while maintaining pricing inefficiencies that sophisticated arbitrageurs can exploit."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT funding rates on Bybit have shown cyclical patterns correlating with broader Layer 1 sentiment and Sui network milestones. During bullish periods, funding rates frequently turn positive (longs pay shorts) as retail traders accumulate leveraged long positions. The token's relatively recent market introduction means historical data spans fewer cycles than established assets, but observable patterns include elevated funding during major exchange listings and ecosystem announcements. Weekend funding periods often show reduced volatility compared to traditional market hours."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Optimal SUI funding arbitrage on Bybit emerges when rates deviate significantly from the 8-hour average of competing exchanges. Traders can capture funding payments by holding opposite positions across venues or employing delta-neutral strategies using spot SUI holdings. Bybit's unified trading account facilitates cross-margin calculations, reducing capital requirements for arbitrage positions. The exchange's fast matching engine ensures minimal slippage during position entries, critical for maintaining hedge ratios in volatile Layer 1 tokens like SUI."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI funding arbitrage carries specific risks including the token's correlation with Solana ecosystem performance and broader smart contract platform sentiment. Sudden network issues or competitive threats from other Layer 1s can trigger rapid price movements that overwhelm funding rate gains. Bybit's auto-deleveraging system activates during extreme market stress, potentially closing arbitrage positions at unfavorable levels. Position sizing should account for SUI's higher volatility compared to major cryptocurrencies, with stop-losses calibrated for the token's average daily ranges."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Bybit settle SUI/USDT funding rates?","answer":"Bybit settles SUI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The funding fee is calculated based on the 8-hour time-weighted average premium and exchanged directly between traders holding opposite positions."},{"question":"What are typical SUI funding rate ranges on Bybit?","answer":"SUI funding rates on Bybit typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, though extreme market conditions can push rates to the ±0.75% caps. During network developments or major partnerships, sustained positive funding above 0.1% is common as retail interest drives long-side demand."},{"question":"Can I use spot SUI holdings for funding arbitrage on Bybit?","answer":"Yes, Bybit's unified trading account allows you to hold spot SUI while taking short perpetual positions to capture funding payments. This delta-neutral strategy eliminates directional price risk while collecting funding fees from overleveraged long traders during positive funding periods."},{"question":"How does SUI funding compare to other Layer 1 tokens on Bybit?","answer":"SUI funding rates generally exhibit higher volatility than established Layer 1s like ETH but lower than newer alternatives. The token's growing ecosystem and Sui network developments create more frequent funding rate dislocations compared to mature smart contract platforms, offering enhanced arbitrage opportunities for active traders."}]}]
